message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the end-to-end delay performance of a satellite-ATM network for TCP/IP traffic. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the trade-off between on-board switching/processing features and the complexity of the satellite communication systems. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper describes the satellite-ATM network architecture. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper discusses a routing algorithm for LEO systems to calculate locally optimal paths for the end-to-end connection. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper presents a simulation model to calculate the buffering delay for TCP/IP traffic over ATM ABR and UBR service categories.
